TITLE: Using getBundlerClient with AccountSigner in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to instantiate an `AccountSigner` using an `EthersProviderAdapter` and a smart account (created via `createLightAccount`). It then calls the `getBundlerClient()` method on the `signer` instance to retrieve the associated `BundlerClient`. This requires dependencies like `@aa-sdk/ethers`, `@aa-sdk/core`, `@account-kit/infra`, `@account-kit/smart-contracts`, and `viem`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/alchemyplatform/aa-sdk/blob/main/docs/pages/reference/aa-sdk/ethers/classes/AccountSigner/getBundlerClient.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

