TITLE: Passing the Account to Client Methods
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use a smart account with a client by passing the account directly to client methods. It shows the createSmartAccountClientFromExisting helper and how to send user operations with an explicit account parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/alchemyplatform/aa-sdk/blob/main/site/pages/migration-guide.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createLightAccount } from "@account-kit/smart-contracts";
import {
  createBundlerClient,
  createSmartAccountClientFromExisting
  LocalAccountSigner,
  type Hex,
} from "@aa-sdk/core";
import { sepolia } from "@aa-sdk/core";
import { custom, http } from "viem";

const chain = sepolia;

const client = createBundlerClient({
  chain,
  transport: http("JSON_RPC_URL"),
});

// [!code focus:99]
// createSmartAccountClientFromExisting is a helper method that allows you
// to reuse a JSON RPC client to create a Smart Account client.
const smartAccountClient = createSmartAccountClientFromExisting({
  client,
});

const account = await createLightAccount({
  signer,
  chain,
  transport: custom(client),
});

const { hash } = await smartAccountClient.sendUserOperation({
    uo: {
        target: "0xdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeefdeadbeef",
        data: "0x",
        value: 10n,
    },
    account, // [!code ++]
});
```

