TITLE: Defining Rule Types in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Schema for different types of rules including method-based, recipient-based, and contract-based rules. Each rule type specifies allowed or denied actions with associated conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/alchemyplatform/aa-sdk/blob/main/docs/pages/signer/policies/offchain-policy-configuration.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
type Rule =
  | {
      name: string;
      type: "methods";
      action: "ALLOW" | "DENY";
      method:
        | "eth_signTransaction" // EVM only
        | "sign_operation" // EVM only
        | "wallet_prepareCalls" // EVM only https://github.com/ethereum/ERCs/pull/758
        | "wallet_sendPreparedCalls" // EVM only https://github.com/ethereum/ERCs/pull/758
        | "signAndSendTransaction" // SVM only
        | "sendTransaction"; // SVM only
      conditions: Condition[];
    }
  | {
      type: "recipients";
      action: "ALLOW" | "DENY";
      address: string[];
    }
  | {
      type: "contracts";
      action: "ALLOW" | "DENY";
      address: string[];
    };
```

